# Cloudflare SSH CA public key — the "Global Certificate Authority used by your
# infrastructure applications for SSH with Access for Infrastructure". sshd's
# TrustedUserCAKeys (via services.openssh-ca-trust on nixpi) trusts short-lived
# certificates signed by this CA. This is the CA's PUBLIC key — safe to commit.
#
# There is no Terraform resource for the CA; it is generated/held by Cloudflare
# and filled in here by hand. Retrieved 2026-07-08 from the account's
# Access-for-Infrastructure SSH CA (id 9e39e11c-8da7-4a39-b6c9-a6f97d5751dd) via
# GET /accounts/<account>/access/gateway_ca. Re-fetch there if it is ever rotated.
ecdsa-sha2-nistp256 AAAAE2VjZHNhLXNoYTItbmlzdHAyNTYAAAAIbmlzdHAyNTYAAABBBDOkmplEgxfceH9lIP+Kt/JwyKjqtn8fVLmoUP0KCp4MTu7fbw0R+VoI24HO8j36dgsJm7kL4yBbV8Hmf9+/LsY= open-ssh-ca@cloudflareaccess.org
